reviewText: This was a $2.00 item (the first season) that my gram picked-up at a "Dollar" store.  The plot, theme, actors...excellent!  It was as great as "6 Feet Under"..."Weeds"...and many others in that style.  I had to buy season #2 (via Amazon for more than 2 bucks) and it was as exciting and intersting as the first season.  Psychological, people related, fun, scary...human relationships....the ending may not be completed because many people who watched this series....i think on ShowTime wanted more; our family, however, felt that the ending was wonderful and appropriate!Totally well worth series...we marathoned it!
Title: Huff: Season 2

reviewText: Series 1, 4 real DVDs; Series 2, 3 DVD-R's--a real terrible, very pixellated transfer of 13 episodes, each hour at about only 1.4 GB each, a VERY un-dense and thin transfer, so the show looks blotchy and fuzzy and grainy and pixellated.  Still, having this thirtysomething/House-like drama is better than nothing, but get it from your local library or through ILL instead and transfer it yourself rather than buying it from SONY.
summary: Great show, great house, awful transfer.
Title: Huff: Season 2

reviewText: I bought season one at at discount store because it had Anton Yeltsin in it.I was really surprised by thiis three disc set and now have purchased season two.Great psychiatry, crazy friendships, drugs & rock anf roll party style, and marriage difficulties.All the charactgers are excellent. Don not miss this one
summary: Huff- How did I miss it?

reviewText: From the first 20 minutes of this show , you're hooked .  The characters are magnetic and draw you into the story that fast .  This not a show for the light hearted or for children .  It is a cleverly written for the mature adults whom appreciate good entertainment.
Title: Huff: Season 2

reviewText: The 2nd season of this series, Huff, was quickly cancelled, but stellar nonetheless. The summation was a gift from the Gods. It looked like it wasn't going to get made, but wonderfully, it did. Great show. Even better ending.
summary: So glad I got the last season of Huff.
